#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:1
msgid "Seat Allocation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:3
msgid ""
"Once the iterative proportional election is complete, parliamentary seats"
" are distributed among the parties. The procedure distinguishes two "
"cases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:7
msgid "Case 1 — Winner Receives an Assigned Majority"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:9
msgid ""
"**Condition:** The winning party (or coalition) did *not* reach the "
"parliament majority threshold by directly exceeding it in the final "
"round. This applies when:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:11
msgid ""
"the winner was determined through party elimination across multiple "
"rounds or by drawing of lots, **or**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:12
msgid ""
"the winner exceeded the ballot threshold (e.g. 52 %) but falls below the "
"parliament majority threshold (e.g. 55 %)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:14
msgid "**Procedure:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:16
msgid ""
"The winner receives exactly as many seats as are required for a "
"parliament majority (retrievable via "
"`ElectionConfig.getParliamentMajoritySeats()`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:17
msgid ""
"The remaining seats are distributed proportionally among the **other "
"parties** — based on their vote shares in the **first round** (before any"
" coalition formation or party elimination)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:19
msgid ""
"The first-round result is used because it most directly reflects the will"
" of the voters: all parties were still competing, and no voter had to "
"vote tactically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:23
msgid "Case 2 — Proportional Distribution of All Seats"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:25
msgid ""
"**Condition:** The winner exceeded the parliament majority threshold "
"through a clear victory in the final round."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:27
msgid ""
"**Procedure:** All parliamentary seats are distributed proportionally "
"according to the result of the **final round**. Coalition votes are "
"counted together."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:31
msgid "Coalitions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:33
msgid ""
"If a coalition has won seats, these are — after the overall allocation — "
"distributed proportionally among the coalition members. The weights used "
"are the member parties' vote weights from the round in which the "
"coalition was formed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:37
msgid "Seat Distribution Method"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:39
msgid ""
"Seats are indivisible. A purely proportional calculation typically yields"
" fractional numbers (e.g. \"Party A deserves 12.7 seats\"), which must be"
" rounded to whole numbers without changing the total. Different rounding "
"methods treat these fractions differently and tend to favour either "
"larger or smaller parties. Such a method is called an apportionment "
"method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:41
msgid ""
"For proportional allocation (both of the total seats and within "
"coalitions), an apportionment method is applied. The method is configured"
" via the `seat_distribution_method` parameter in "
"[`ElectionEvaluator`](../../../src/ipres/election_evaluator.py). The "
"available options are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md
msgid "Method"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md
msgid "`SAINTE_LAGUE` *(default)*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md
msgid ""
"Sainte-Laguë/Schepers method, also known as the Webster method. Used by "
"the German Bundestag. Favours neither large nor small parties."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md
msgid "`D_HONDT`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md
msgid ""
"D'Hondt method (highest averages). Used in many European countries. "
"Slightly favours larger parties."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md
msgid "`HARE_NIEMEYER`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md
msgid ""
"Hare-Niemeyer method (largest remainder). First allocates seats based on "
"the integer part of each party's quota, then awards remaining seats to "
"the parties with the largest remainders."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/en/seat_allocation.md:49
msgid ""
"For links to further references see "
"[`SeatDistributionMethod`](global_configuration.md) in the global "
"configuration."
msgstr ""

